Disclaimer and Contribution Guidelines

Thank you for your interest in contributing to this project! Please read and follow these guidelines to ensure smooth collaboration and maintain the integrity of the repository.

1. No Direct Commits Without Output Verification

    Before committing any changes, you must verify the output of your modifications. This ensures that the project remains stable and functional.
    Once you have tested your changes and confirmed they work as expected, submit your changes for review. Any unverified or unreviewed commits may be rejected.

2. Do Not Alter Original Files

    The original files in this repository must remain unchanged. This is essential to maintain the project's core functionality and integrity.
    If you need to implement changes or new features, do not directly modify the original files. Instead, follow the process outlined below for making changes.

3. Clone the Project and Make Changes

    If you wish to contribute, clone this repository to your local environment.
    Make your changes in a separate branch or your cloned version. Once you are satisfied with your modifications, you can submit a pull request for review.
    Clearly document all changes in your pull request and explain how your modifications improve the project or solve a problem.

4. License

    This project is licensed under [insert license type]. By contributing, you agree to adhere to the terms of this license.

5. Code of Conduct

    We expect all contributors to maintain respectful and professional communication at all times.
    Abusive, inappropriate, or non-constructive behavior will not be tolerated, and violators may be removed from the project.

6. Issue Reporting

    If you encounter any bugs or issues, please open an issue using the repository's issue tracker. Be sure to provide detailed information to help resolve the issue efficiently.

By following these guidelines, you help maintain the quality of this project and ensure a positive collaboration experience for everyone. Thank you!
